Milestone Controller

Base URL: /api/milestones

1. Create a Milestone
Endpoint: /api/milestones
Method: POST
Description: Creates a new milestone.

Request Body:
`json`
{
  "id": <Long>,
  "name": <String>,
  "description": <String>,
  "dueDate": <String>  // ISO 8601 format (e.g., "2025-01-01T12:00:00Z")
}
Response:
Status Code: 201 Created
Body: Returns the created milestone.
`json`
{
  "id": <Long>,
  "name": <String>,
  "description": <String>,
  "dueDate": <String>
}

2. Update a Milestone
Endpoint: /api/milestones/{milestoneId}
Method: PUT
Description: Updates an existing milestone by its ID.

Path Parameter: milestoneId (Long): The ID of the milestone to update.
Request Body:
`json`
{
  "name": <String>,
  "description": <String>,
  "dueDate": <String>
}
Response:
Status Code: 200 OK
Body: Returns the updated milestone.
`json`
{
  "id": <Long>,
  "name": <String>,
  "description": <String>,
  "dueDate": <String>
}

3. Get a Milestone by ID
Endpoint: /api/milestones/{milestoneId}
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves a specific milestone by its ID.

Path Parameter: milestoneId (Long): The ID of the milestone to retrieve.
Response: Status Code: 200 OK
Body:
`json`
{
  "id": <Long>,
  "name": <String>,
  "description": <String>,
  "dueDate": <String>
}
Status Code: 404 Not Found
Returns no body if the milestone is not found.

4. Get All Milestones
Endpoint: /api/milestones
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves all milestones.

Response:
Status Code: 200 OK
Body: Returns a list of milestones.
`json`
[
  {
    "id": <Long>,
    "name": <String>,
    "description": <String>,
    "dueDate": <String>
  },
  ...
]

5. Delete a Milestone
Endpoint: /api/milestones/{milestoneId}
Method: DELETE
Description: Deletes a milestone by its ID.

Path Parameter: milestoneId (Long): The ID of the milestone to delete.
Response: Status Code: 204 No Content